As of version 1.2, you may now set your own sounds for the game.  To do this, extract the file @{u}ms@{uu} from the sources archive.  Take your 8SVX files which you want as your sounds and rename them "explosion.8svx", "start.8svx", and "shoot.8svx".  Make a backup copy of your original Sounds.8svx file, and run the ms program.  The next time that you run DogFight!, your new sounds will be used.  I make no guarantees that your sounds will work with DogFight!.  However, if you keep the sounds reasonably short and have enough memory for them, there should be no problems.  Important is that the three sound files are in standard IFF-8SVX format.

